con:testSuite.con:setupScript:
String env = context.expand('${#Project#env}')
log.info "Environment is $env"
//load the configuration file based on environment (dev, or prod)
String filePath = "C:\\Users\\dsharman2\\Music\\Introduction to API Testing - ReadyAPI\\REST Projects\\config Files\\"+env+".properties"
log.info "Loading file $filePath"
Properties props = new Properties()
//loop through file content and load properties.
File configFile =new File(filePath)
configFile.withInputStream{
line->
props.load(line) } log.info props['bankEndpoint']
log.info props['supplierEndpoint']
testSuite.project.setPropertyValue('bankEndpoint',props['bankEndpoint'])
testSuite.project.setPropertyValue('supplierEndpoint',props['supplierEndpoint'])
